        "title": "feat(gateway): emit config.changed event with diff on hot-reload",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds `config.changed` gateway event (ADMIN scope) emitted to connected clients when config hot-reloads\n- Payload includes a structured diff: changed paths with before/after values, added keys, removed keys\n- Sensitive values (keys containing \"key\", \"token\", \"secret\", \"password\", or \"credential\") are redacted in the diff payload\n- Diff depth capped at 4 levels to avoid noise from large nested config objects\n- Uses existing `registerRuntimeConfigWriteListener` and `broadcastGatewayEvent` infrastructure; no new storage required\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Config hot-reload emits `config.changed` event to connected admin-scoped clients\n- [ ] Changed model name appears in diff with before/after values\n- [ ] API keys are redacted in diff output\n- [ ] No event emitted when config write produces identical content\n- [ ] `pnpm check:changed` passes\n\nThanks @ioodu",
